gten Werkes.  aWithin the scope of the Greek-Latin Alexander romance, the Res gestae Alexandri Macedonis by Julius Valerius (early fourth century CE) stand out due to their high literary and stylistic standards. The eleven contributions in this edited volume primarily focus on issues of narrative technique, linguistic design, and intertextuality, thereby illustrating the unique features and rank of this often-neglected work in literary history.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAlexander der Große. 4aIulius Valerius. 4aMittelatein. 4aSpätantike. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAlexander the Great.  aIulius Valerius.  aLate Antiquity.  aMiddle Latin.1 aAmmann, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrenez, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDjurslev, Christian Thrue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez, M.ª Carmen Puche, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwameis, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchöffberger, Gregor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchön, Katharina-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiemoneit, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteinmann, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStoneman, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWulfram, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https